<Class name="CM_RailLine" id="42e22738-614f-48dc-a266-cf63b82fe8e9">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>New class to model the new rail rakes.
This class represents a single rail line. It contains the locationsControllers
as well as the dimensions of the actual line like its parent area- a CM_Rail object
which is the TA.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="location"/>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="allIncompleteWLEs" id="b2197812-0379-46ad-84b3-51758bb8739e">
        <memberTypeInverse/>
        <type name="CM_WLEArray"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>This is a collection by rake of WLE's that have been set to
the "rake" position by the radio telemetry interface.
when the driver cannot give us the wagon# or rake position, we shift the
ti to the RTA, then add an entry into this collection, for the rake of the
wle that is in an "incomplete" state.
Once the TI s shifted to a wagon pos, we remove this entry.
They CANNOT clear a rake UNTIL there are NO WLEs unactioned in
the list for the rake.
DQ 04 feb 1999.
Added to this class 17 July 2001 DQ</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
